{
  "texts": [
    "Adding ambiguity in the distribution of potential payoffs or changing their magnitude has little effect as long as the relative value of options is maintained.",
    "Third, we endow a subset of AI agents with heterogeneous preferences and objectives.",
    "In so doing, we see that even a small share of agents with alternative preferences can temper the streetlight effect.",
    "In a final set of experiments, we simply ask out-of-the-box LLMs to predict the results of the experiment rather than using the GABE approach we propose.",
    "We show how this approach has limited power to predict real-world outcomes to the same extent."
  ]
}